text.tspan: Vectual
Vectual
Vectual
Welcome to The Open Source Charting Library

flowRoot.flowPara: In contrast to other charting libraries, which are build upon flash or are commercial, Vectual is solely based on the newest web standards! So even your cell phones and your tablets are able to display the beautiful charts!

Today the Internet is producing billions of data each day! Billions of numbers and values give a precise image of what's going on in the world! But How can a human being understand and interpret all those numbers and values?
That's what vectual does! Vectual is a open source charting library. It visualizes data and helps you to understand it!

flowRoot.flowPara: The whole Library will get released as Open Source Software, so that you will be able to use it for all of your projects! Both non-profit and commercial!
Please help me to make the world a little more open and help me to build this awesome piece of software!
The most important ingredient for such a huge project is time and you can give me the time it takes to iron out such a powerful tool!

By pledging you guarantee that I don't have to spend my leisure time with pointless summer jobs, just to be able to pay the next slice of pizza, all the energy drinks a programmer needs or to finance my studies!
Furthermore I need to purchase domains, pay the servers, etc. to be able to get vectual running!

Vectual doesn't have to be limited to static visualization. Imagine realtime charts, multidimensional charts or even charts which can be played like a video to show certain data over time! But all those ideas, plans and visions which grew in my head over the last few month need your support to get realized!
Please check out www.vectual.org for Demos and further Information!
Thank you very much for your support!
